      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAWBOURNE LADY (1) could manage only second at this track last time but turned heads when posting a blistering 29.96 over 525m at this track the start prior. Rates on top and can find winning form again. MANSON LAMPS (7) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 30.12 beating CAWBOURNE LADY. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from three starts. Deserves serious consideration again. PAW YUSAMI (3) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close second, 2 lengths from the winner State Of Madness (31.02) at Broken Hill. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Well placed and gets her chance. CAWBOURNE PIP (2) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
